Fundus Anatomy
=====

>>The optic disc is...<<
[[
temporal (lateral) to the macula, 
(nasal (medial)  macula)
temporal (lateral) and in the same horizontal plane compared with the macula
nasal
]]

>>The optic disc is...<<
[[(in the same horizontal plane as the macula),
superior to the macula,
inferior to the macula]]

>>Therefore when finding the optic disc during funduscopy you should aim your funduscope...<<
[[(in the horizontal axis of the patient's line of sight, and towards the nose),
above the patient's line of sight, and towards the nose,
in the axis of the patient's line of sight, and towards the temple/ear]]

>>Retinal vessels all enter the eye via:<<
[[(the nasal side of the optic disc),
the macula, the temporal side of the optic disc
the iris]]

>>Retinal vessels bifurcate (divide):<<
[[(away from the optic disc),
towards the optic disc,
towards the macula,
towards the iris]]

>>Therefore when finding the optic disc during funduscopy you should aim your funduscope...<<
[[(the opposite direction to a bifurcating vessel),
the same direction as a bifurcating vessel,
in the axis of the patient's line of sight, and towards the temple/ear]]
